#include <linux/module.h>
#include <linux/miscdevice.h>
#include <linux/err.h>
#include <linux/gpio.h>
#include <linux/gpio/consumer.h>
#include <linux/kernel.h>
#include <linux/leds.h>
#include <linux/module.h>
#include <linux/of.h>
#include <linux/platform_device.h>
#include <linux/property.h>
#include <linux/slab.h>
#include <linux/init.h>
#include <asm/types.h>
#include <linux/uaccess.h>
#include <linux/of_gpio.h>
#include <linux/miscdevice.h>
#define CMD_SWITCH_STATE 0
#define CMD_GET_STATE 1
#define RSR485_RECEIVER_STATE 0
#define RSR485_SENDER_STATE 1
static DEFINE_MUTEX(relay_mutex_lock);
static int ctrl_gpio;
static int relay_ioctl(struct file *file, unsigned int cmd, unsigned long arg)
{
	int ret = 0;
	switch (cmd) {
	case CMD_SWITCH_STATE:
		gpio_set_value(ctrl_gpio, arg);
		if (gpio_get_value(ctrl_gpio) != arg) {
			printk("[debug] gpio set value failed:%d\n", ret);
			return -1;
		}
		printk("[debug] gpio set value %ld success\n", arg);
		break;
	case CMD_GET_STATE:
		ret = gpio_get_value(ctrl_gpio);
		if (ret < 0) {
			printk("[debug] gpio get value failed:%d\n", ret);
			return -1;
		}
		if (copy_to_user((int *)arg, &ret, sizeof(int))) {
			printk("copy data to user space failed!\n");
			return -1;
		}
		break;
	}
	return 0;
}
static int relay_open(struct inode *inode, struct file *file)
{
	return nonseekable_open(inode, file);
}
static long relay_unlocked_ioctl(struct file *file, unsigned int cmd,
				 unsigned long arg)
{
	int ret;
	mutex_lock(&relay_mutex_lock);
	ret = relay_ioctl(file, cmd, arg);
	mutex_unlock(&relay_mutex_lock);
	return ret;
}
static const struct file_operations relay_fops = {
	.owner = THIS_MODULE,
	.open = relay_open,
	.unlocked_ioctl = relay_unlocked_ioctl,
};
static struct miscdevice relay_miscdev = { MISC_DYNAMIC_MINOR, "relay_ctl",
					   &relay_fops };
static const struct of_device_id of_relay_ctl_match[] = {
	{
		.compatible = "relay_ctl",
	},
	{},
};
MODULE_DEVICE_TABLE(of, of_relay_ctl_match);
static int relay_ctl_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
{
	int ret;
	struct device *dev;
	printk("[debug] relay_ctl_probe");
	dev = &pdev->dev;
	
	ctrl_gpio = of_get_named_gpio(dev->of_node, "gpios", 0);
	if (!gpio_is_valid(ctrl_gpio)) {
		printk("of_get_named_gpio is error \n");
		return -1;
	}
	ret = devm_gpio_request(dev, ctrl_gpio, "relay_ctl");
	if (ret < 0) {
		dev_err(&pdev->dev, "failed to request GPIO#%d: %d\n",
			ctrl_gpio, ret);
		return -1;
	}
	gpio_direction_output(ctrl_gpio, 1);
	ret = misc_register(&relay_miscdev);
	if (ret < 0)
		return ret;
	return 0;
}
static int relay_ctl_remove(struct platform_device *pdev)
{
	printk("[debug] relay_ctl_shutdown");
	misc_deregister(&relay_miscdev);
	return 0;
}
static struct platform_driver relay_ctl_driver = {
	.probe		= relay_ctl_probe,
	.remove		= relay_ctl_remove,
	.driver		= {
		.name	= "relay-ctl-gpio",
		.of_match_table = of_relay_ctl_match,
	},
};
module_platform_driver(relay_ctl_driver);
MODULE_DESCRIPTION("GPIO relay ctl driver");
MODULE_LICENSE("GPL");
MODULE_ALIAS("platform:relay_ctl");

                printf("open error\n");

        len = strlen(val);
        ret = write(fd, val, len);
        if(ret < 0)
        {
                printf("write error\n");
                return -1;

        close(fd);
        return 0;
}
